cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the theoretical limits of what can be learned by neural networks. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as neural networks are a fundamental component of AI. Additionally, since the paper discusses adversarial attacks on neural networks, it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as image classification is a common application of neural networks in computer vision. It could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as the paper discusses the deployment of neural networks in security critical settings. Finally, it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with the theoretical analysis of neural networks.
